entries.femaleVariant: Come in, come in! Ah, raised you, finally.
I need your help.
Then why don't you?
Why can't you?
I need your help. One last time.
Hm. Right place, right time – you were there?
Huh, actually left a message. He's waiting on a farm. Flickin' you the geoloc data.
Willie McCoy. It's good to hear your voice.
V. Wish I could say the same.
You abandoned the clan, I can't help you anymore.
Nomads get the work in these parts because it's nomad turf. Wouldn't be a problem if you were still a Bakker.
Thanks, Willie. I owe ya one.
You do. Just don't get yourself killed. And don't call again.
"One last time" – again?
I have to find the client with my payload, but I-I don't know where he is.
entries.maleVariant: I have to find the client with my payload, but I don't know where he is.

entries.femaleVariant: You shoulda stuck with 'em, and joined up with the Snake Nation like the rest.
The Snake Nation can kiss my ass.
Of course.
'Course I was.
My car gave out. The electric coupling – it's a miracle I made it here.
My car broke down.
Maybe the client left a message. Could you check for me?
Hmm...
Sure. Last time, though. I mean it. Client's name?
Jackie Welles.
[Connect to radio station]
Never knew you to be so cautious.
entries.maleVariant: I never knew you to be so cautious.

entries.femaleVariant: Try loyal. Rules are rules, the system won't work without 'em. It can't.
[Open]
[Open]
[Kick]
[Stop leaning]
